html.body: <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> CycD1/CDK4,6/p27 and CycE1/CDK2 complexes phosphorylate p130 which leads to the dissociation of the E2F4/p130 complex => entry in G1. CycD1/CDK4,6/p27 phosphorylates p107

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> CycD1/CDK4,6/p27 and CycE1/CDK2 complexes phosphorylate p130 which leads to the dissociation of the E2F4/p130 complex => entry in G1.

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> p130_pho and p107 can inhibit both CycA2/CDK2 and CycE1/CDK2

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> p130_pho free and p107 can inhibit both CycE1/CDK2 and CycA2/CDK2

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> Both DP1 and E2F1 are phosphorylated by CycA2/CDK2 complex at Ser-375, which diminishes the affinity between E2F1 and DP1

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> pRB binds to E2F1/DP1 to repress its transcription potential.

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> phosphorylations by CycC/CDK3 induces the G0/G1 transition

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> Phosphorylation by CycD/p27/CDK4,6 modifies the conformation of pRB

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> CycE/CDK2 phosphorylates both pRB and BRG1 present in the SWI/SNF complex. The hyperphosphorylation of pRB decreases its affinity with E2F1/DP1 and the complex dissociates.

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> In the case of CycD1/CDK4,6, p27 stabilizes the CDK complex. The trimer (CDK4,6 in the trimer) is phosphorylated by CycH and stimulates its CAK complex activity. The phosphorylated form seems to have a kinase activity on the pocket proteins, pRB, p130 and p107. p27Kip1 favors the transport to the nucleus of CycD1/CDK4,6.

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> p27Kip1 and p21Cip1 are cyclin-dependent kinase inhibitors. They associate with the CDK complexes composed of a kinase and a cyclin partner, CycE1/CDK2, CycA2/CDK2 and CycD1/CDK4,6 to form an inactive trimer.

They associate with the CDK complexes composed of a kinase and a cyclin partner, CycE1/CDK2, CycA2/CDK2 and CycD1/CDK4,6 to form an inactive trimer.

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> p27Kip1 is phosphorylated by CycE1/CDK2 at Thr-187, which results in targeting p27 for its degradation by proteolysis

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> p16 and p15 are kinase inhibitors. They are located in the cytoplasm where they sequester CDK6 and CDK4, preventing the binding of the kinase with its cyclin partner CycD1

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> The active complex phosphorylates and activates CycD1/CDK4,6, CycE1/CDK2, CycA2/CDK2, and CycB1/CDC2.

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> Cdc20 is phosphorylated by CycB1/CDC2_Thr161. Cdc20 phosphorylated can then bind to APC and it is the APC/CDC20P who is active.

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> CDC20 phosphorylated can tag CycB1 and CycA2 (during M phase) for degradation

APC/Cdh1 degrades CycA2, if present, during G1 phase

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> Cdh1 is dephosphorylated by the phosphatase Cdc14 and phosphorylated and kept inactive by CycA2/CDK2. This arrow doesn't concern CDC20

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> p14 sequesters E2F1 and prevents transcription of cell cycle genes (block in G1).

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> Chek1 and 2 phosphorylates E2F1/DP1/PCAF and stabilize the complex (it facilitates its binding to 14-3-3 tau)

<body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <body xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> Chek1 & 2 phosphorylate CDC25C and Wee1 and arrest cell cycle at G2/M transition until damage is repaired
